# Professional Proctoring System — Implementation Plan

Build a remote proctoring feature for an Olympiad website. Contestants share camera + screen; Admin monitors all participants in a real-time grid with incident alerts.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **LiveKit Credentials**: You will need a LiveKit server (self-hosted or cloud) with `LIVEKIT_API_KEY`, `LIVEKIT_API_SECRET`, and `LIVEKIT_URL`. These go into `.env.local`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Firebase**: You will need a Firebase project with Firestore enabled. The client config values go into `.env.local`.

> [!WARNING]
> **Auth**: The plan uses a **lightweight role-based approach** (role sent in the token request body). For production, you'd integrate with NextAuth.js or Firebase Auth. Should I implement full auth now, or keep it simple with role-based token grants?

## Proposed Changes

### Scaffolding

#### [NEW] Next.js 15 project (App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS)
Scaffold with `npx create-next-app@latest` using TypeScript + Tailwind + App Router.

#### [NEW] [.env.example](file:///d:/github%20projects/emo-competition-app/.env.example)
Template with all required env vars:
```
LIVEKIT_API_KEY=
LIVEKIT_API_SECRET=
LIVEKIT_URL=wss://your-livekit-server.example.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_LIVEKIT_URL=wss://your-livekit-server.example.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
```

---

### Core Infrastructure

#### [NEW] [types/proctoring.ts](file:///d:/github%20projects/emo-competition-app/src/types/proctoring.ts)
TypeScript interfaces for the Firestore data schema:
- **Room** — `{ id, name, status, createdAt, adminId }`
- **Participant** — `{ id, roomId, displayName, role, joinedAt, isScreenSharing, isCameraOn }`
- **Incident** — `{ id, roomId, participantId, participantName, type, message, timestamp }`

Incident types: `'tab-switch' | 'screen-share-stopped' | 'camera-off' | 'manual'`

#### [NEW] [lib/firebase.ts](file:///d:/github%20projects/emo-competition-app/src/lib/firebase.ts)
Initialize Firebase app & export Firestore `db` instance. Client-side only.

#### [NEW] [lib/firestore.ts](file:///d:/github%20projects/emo-competition-app/src/lib/firestore.ts)
Helper functions:
- `logIncident(incident)` — add doc to `rooms/{roomId}/incidents`
- `subscribeToIncidents(roomId, callback)` — `onSnapshot` listener

---

### Token Generation API

#### [NEW] [app/api/livekit-token/route.ts](file:///d:/github%20projects/emo-competition-app/src/app/api/livekit-token/route.ts)
POST endpoint accepting `{ roomName, participantName, role }`:
- Uses `AccessToken` from `livekit-server-sdk`
- **Contestant**: `canPublish: true`, `canSubscribe: false`, `canPublishSources: ['camera', 'screen_share']`
- **Admin**: `canPublish: false`, `canSubscribe: true`, `roomAdmin: true`
- Returns `{ token: string }`

---

### Contestant View

#### [NEW] [components/proctoring/ContestantRoom.tsx](file:///d:/github%20projects/emo-competition-app/src/components/proctoring/ContestantRoom.tsx)
`"use client"` component. Key behaviors:
1. On mount → POST to `/api/livekit-token` to get token
2. Connect to `<LiveKitRoom>` with `video={true}` (360p resolution constraint)
3. Auto-request screen share via `localParticipant.setScreenShareEnabled(true)`
4. **Screen share stop** → set `examLocked = true`, blur overlay on exam, log incident
5. **`visibilitychange`** listener → if `document.hidden`, log `tab-switch` incident to Firestore
6. Status indicators for camera/screen share status
7. Exam content area (placeholder) that blurs when locked

#### [NEW] [app/contestant/[roomName]/page.tsx](file:///d:/github%20projects/emo-competition-app/src/app/contestant/[roomName]/page.tsx)
Page route that renders `<ContestantRoom>` with `roomName` from params.

---

### Admin Dashboard

#### [NEW] [components/proctoring/ParticipantTile.tsx](file:///d:/github%20projects/emo-competition-app/src/components/proctoring/ParticipantTile.tsx)
Single participant card:
- Screen share track → main background `<VideoTrack>`
- Camera track → small PiP overlay in corner `<VideoTrack>`
- Name label + status indicators

#### [NEW] [components/proctoring/AdminGrid.tsx](file:///d:/github%20projects/emo-competition-app/src/components/proctoring/AdminGrid.tsx)
`"use client"` component:
- `<LiveKitRoom>` with `manageSubscription={true}` (lazy subscriptions)
- `useParticipants()` to list all remote participants
- Responsive CSS grid (auto-fill, minmax 320px)
- Maps participants to `<ParticipantTile>`

#### [NEW] [components/proctoring/IncidentsSidebar.tsx](file:///d:/github%20projects/emo-competition-app/src/components/proctoring/IncidentsSidebar.tsx)
`"use client"` component:
- `onSnapshot` on `rooms/{roomId}/incidents` (ordered by timestamp desc)
- Real-time scrolling list with severity-colored badges
- Filter by incident type

#### [NEW] [app/admin/[roomName]/page.tsx](file:///d:/github%20projects/emo-competition-app/src/app/admin/[roomName]/page.tsx)
Page route: sidebar + grid layout. Fetches admin token and renders `<AdminGrid>` + `<IncidentsSidebar>`.

